enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve managing indication listeners for specific local addresses, making them complementary for setting up and tearing down test environments.
Both methods involve managing indication listeners, though for different types of indications, making them useful for comprehensive test coverage.
The handleMessageEvent method processes incoming messages, which can be used to simulate incoming indications that would trigger the need to remove a listener.
The fireMessageEvent method triggers message events, which can be used to simulate the conditions under which an indication listener might need to be removed.
